<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_OwnableRestaurants" s="141798">
  <T n="name">0x9F84C66D<!--String: "Restaurants - Ownership"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_ownership_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d89e8577bb7c458a</T>
      <T n="text">0xD6B487DF<!--String: "Sims can own and manage restaurants to earn Simoleons. To open a restaurant, use the Phone or Computer and select "Buy Restaurant." You can buy an existing restaurant, or purchase any unoccupied lot and start from scratch.\n\nA household can own and run multiple restaurants at the same time. Go ahead and try to create your culinary empire.\n"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_ownership_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d89e8577bb7c4589</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial_controller\restaurant_ownership_2_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:36323625245ed2c4</T>
      <T n="text">0x5C48D010<!--String: "When you first arrive at your restaurant you'll be asked to transfer some funds to your business to cover basic operating expenses. To learn more about managing your money, read the "Restaurant - Funds" lesson."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_ownership_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d89e8577bb7c4588</T>
      <T n="text">0xD7A78120<!--String: "You'll need a functioning restaurant before you can open the doors. This means placing and staffing a chef station, a waiter station, and a host station. You will also need to place at least 4 dining spots, a bathroom, and a sink. Next, you will need to customize your menu."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_ownership_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d89e8577bb7c458f</T>
      <T n="text">0xD390DA2A<!--String: "Check out the Owned Businesses panel in the bottom right hand corner. This is where you open and close your restaurant. You will find useful information and shortcuts that will help you customize and run your restaurant."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_ownership_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d89e8577bb7c458e</T>
      <T n="text">0xD36F2F12<!--String: "Your customers will be rating their dining experience from 1 to 5 stars. These ratings will determine your restaurant's overall star rating which will go on to determine how many more customers will come to eat there.\n\nThe customers will be paying attention to the ambiance of the dining room, how well they are treated by the host, how long they have to wait for food, and more. Read the "Restaurants - Ratings" lesson for more tips on how to effectively keep your diners happy."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_ownership_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d89e8577bb7c458d</T>
      <T n="text">0x578C1B7A<!--String: "If you decide you no longer want to run your restaurant, you may offload it by using the "Sell this Business" interaction on the Restaurant Settings panel. Your restaurant's funds will be added to the value of the lot and get refunded to your household. Once you've sold your restaurant, it will continue to run under new management, and you can visit it in the future as a customer!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_GP03_DineOut</E>
  </L>
</I>